RISING STAR WITH NET CASH OF $30M VERSUS MARKET CAP OF $10MI am highlighting 1 Stock in the Consumer Staples Food Snacks business called CHINA STAR FOOD. Many people have tell me to avoid Chinese S-chips listed on SGX but many may not know that it is a local incorporated company in the 'REPUBLIC OF SINGAPORE'. With Cash of RMB $150m or $30m SGD sitting in its bank account  China Star Food is basically trading at just one-third of its market cap of $10m. Basicaly you are paying one-third of the price and getting two-third for Free. I analysed the Net Asset Value(NAV) of the company at $0.77RMB or $0.16 SGD cents and it is at trading at a huge discount of 85% vis-a-vas the last done price of $0.024 today. Is this a Value propoistion play leading up to a Potential Merger and Acquistion interest from bigger China consumer staples coy or international coy wanting a Pie of the growing chinese appepite? I remembered back in 2011 Candy Snack maker Hsu Fu Chi was delisted for $2.1b by Nestle.(https://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/nestle-buy-60-singapore-listed-......)China has resume business as per normal after the COVID-19 crisis lockdown in WUHAN lasting from 23 JAN 2020 to 8 APRIL 2020. Many stocks in SGX has sinked to levels not seen before since the Global Financial Crisis in 2009.
